verb.description: Inject liquid into (a subterranean rock formation, borehole, etc.) at high pressure so as to force open existing fissures and extract oil or gas.
examples: millions of gallons of water are needed to successfully frack a single well
a gas company wants to frack his land and the land around it

exclamation.description: Used to express annoyance, frustration, impatience, or surprise.
examples: what the frack is going on!

origin: 1970s: euphemistic alteration of fuck, popularized by the US television show Battlestar Galactica.
